item.title: My Other Computer Flies on A Balloon
item.description: https://loon.co/ We provide internet via huge high-altitude balloons that use winds to navigate and transmit wifi signals between them and back to the ground. They use the stratification of winds in the stratosphere to navigate the world and provide internet to regions are the inaccessible by land. I am currently working as a Flight Engineer at Project Loon. My role is half mission control and half software programming, which pushed me to go back to software.

Connie Mabel Zhang has a bachelor’s in Mechanical Engineering but spends her time flying balloons that provide internet. In her free time she enjoys drawing and playing videogames, and hopes to work on cool new robots in the future.
